cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a protocol for a popular IoT communication protocol, MQTT, and focuses on the distributed architecture of brokers. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the need for distributed solutions for IoT devices and proposes a protocol for distributed MQTT brokers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of a spanning tree for organizing the distributed brokers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed protocol against failures. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper mentions the release of the protocol as an open-source project for reproducible research.
